replyContent: A free fishing mode is a possibility. The reason you start each tournament with limited funds and equipment is for the challenge of seeing how quickly you can work your way up to the best gear.  Keeping the winnings from one tournament to the next would be a bit like starting your second game of Monopoly already owning all the properties.

replyContent: That's actually not a bug.  The amount of money you start with varies from $40 to $50 in the premium version ($20 to $25 in the old free version.)  The reason for the variation is to make the shopping more interesting at the start of the game. Rather than buying the same thing every time, it's wise to check your money and see what's on sale.

I have all of Paul's fishing programs on my PC, including this one and my favorite - Real World Fly Fishing.  I like them all, for those days when the stream is just out of reach.  Ice Fishing Derby is an excellent port of the PC version. Unlike RWFF, the graphics are pretty basic. But the gameplay is fun and will have you going for just one more strike before you put it down. It puts you out in the middle of a frozen lake from the warmth of your livingroom. If you're a flyfisherman check out his PC sims.
